{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Metallic Glass",
  "description": "Y2K-aesthetic feedback-displacement metallic surface generator, decomposed from the legacy MetallicGlassGenerator into curated primitives.\n\nUpstream pipeline: 3D simplex noise drives a feedback-blend loop (mix Difference + mix Lerp at 0.98) that builds an evolving liquid-mercury height field; two-axis Gaussian blur smooths the result. The smoothed height feeds (a) a levels-shaped height channel and (b) a mirror_axis → Sobel-magnitude chain that produces an edge / roughness modulation texture. Both channels then go through their own second-stage temporal blend (node.feedback + node.mix Lerp at 0.15) that matches the legacy bundle's packed-material smoothing pass.\n\nTerminal (decomposed 2026-05-27 from the fused node.render_3d_mesh_pbr_ibl bundle): the geometry pass (node.render_3d_mesh, extended with G-buffer outputs) rasterises the displaced mesh and writes world_pos + world_normal alongside its Lambert color (the color output is unused here — only the G-buffer is consumed). A full-resolution world-space surface normal is recomputed from the smoothed height texture via node.heightmap_to_normal (coord_space=WorldYUp, aspect-corrected). The z_scale param is computed in the graph as `aspect / output_width` (matches the legacy `2 * aspect * texel` formula after the helper's built-in 0.5 half-difference). A per-pixel roughness map is derived from the smoothed edge texture via node.scale_offset_texture, mapping edge ∈ [0,1] to roughness ∈ [0.05, 0.20]. node.cook_torrance_specular + node.equirect_envmap_sample then shade per pixel in 3D-mesh mode (world_pos wired from render_3d_mesh.world_pos, view/light wired from camera_orbit.pos_xyz / light_pos params), the two terms are summed via node.mix mode=Add, and node.reinhard_tone_map produces the final SDR output. The env_map upstream stays node.bake_equirect_envmap (the procedural HDR studio).\n\nParity vs legacy bundle: math-equivalent within ≤1 ULP per pixel from atom-decomposition reassociation. The outer-card `displace` slider drives a node.gain on the height feeding heightmap_to_normal, preserving the legacy displacement-coupled normal steepness; inverse-square attenuation scale matches the legacy's 25.0; the second temporal-blend smoothing pass is applied per-channel (height and edge separately) since the decomposed graph no longer has a packed material. z_scale is driven from canvas dimensions matching the legacy texel-based formula.\n\nAtom activations and extensions shipped alongside this decomposition (all reusable for any future PBR-on-3D-mesh preset):\n  - render_3d_mesh: added world_pos + world_normal G-buffer outputs (additive — Lambert color path unchanged)\n  - cook_torrance_specular: added optional world_pos + roughness_map inputs + attenuation_scale param; 3D-mesh mode when world_pos wired\n  - equirect_envmap_sample: added optional world_pos + roughness_map inputs + roughness/metallic/base_color/roughness_scale params (Fresnel + roughness coupling folded into the atom)\n  - heightmap_to_normal: added coord_space enum (TangentZ default | WorldYUp new) + aspect input\n  - camera_orbit: added pos_x/pos_y/pos_z scalar outputs",
  "presetMetadata": {
